//axhob_operation
{scr_security_config}

One unified script executes these commands
in sequence, halting early if any command
has a nonzero unix status:

//axhos_step
1. {scr_iptables_init}
//axhos_step
2. {scr_port_setup}
//axhos_step
3. {scr_access_setup}
//axhos_step
4. {scr_dns_step}

//axhob_operation
{mkr_network_create}

NOTE: Network creation is now managed declaratively by Docker Compose.
The `networks:` section of `rbob_compose.yml` defines both networks; the
{at_enclave_network}
carries a static subnet from the nameplate regime.
Compose creates both the
{at_transit_network}
and
{at_enclave_network}
automatically during `docker compose up`.

The
{at_enclave_network}
uses:

* driver: bridge
* subnet: `${RBRN_ENCLAVE_BASE_IP}/${RBRN_ENCLAVE_NETMASK}` (from nameplate env-file)
* static IPs: sentry at `${RBRN_ENCLAVE_SENTRY_IP}`, pentacle at `${RBRN_ENCLAVE_BOTTLE_IP}`

The
{at_transit_network}
provides internet connectivity via the Docker bridge.
Each nameplate uses a distinct /24 subnet to prevent cross-nameplate collisions.

//axhoc_completion
Both networks are created as part of the compose lifecycle.
The
{at_sentry_container}
connects to both networks; the
{at_pentacle_container}
connects only to the enclave; the
{at_bottle_container}
shares the pentacle's network namespace via compose `network_mode: "service:pentacle"`.

//axhob_operation
{mkr_network_connect}

NOTE: Secondary network attachment is now managed declaratively by Docker Compose.
The sentry's compose service definition lists both
{at_transit_network}
(priority 1000) and
{at_enclave_network}
(priority 500).
Compose attaches both networks when the container starts — there is no separate connect step.

IMPORTANT: Docker Compose does not guarantee which network maps to which interface name (eth0, eth1).
The compose `priority` field influences default route selection but does NOT control interface enumeration order.
The sentry startup script discovers its interfaces by IP using `ip -o addr show to «enclave_ip»` and never references hardcoded interface names.

//axhoc_completion
After compose starts the sentry, it has connectivity on both networks with static IP on the enclave.
Interface-to-network mapping is discovered at runtime, not assumed.

//axhob_operation
{rbsc_charge}

NOTE: This operation starts the full
{at_sessile_service}
via Docker Compose.
Compose owns container and network lifecycle; this operation handles preflight validation, cleanup of prior state, subnet conflict detection, and the compose invocation.

//axhos_step
. *Verify Local Vouch Artifacts*:
.. {rbbc_require}
sentry vouch artifact present in local image store (`docker image inspect` on `<GCP_REGION>-docker.pkg.dev/<PROJECT>/<REPO>/{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/<hallmark>/vouch:<hallmark>`)
.. {rbbc_require}
bottle vouch artifact present in local image store (`docker image inspect` on `<GCP_REGION>-docker.pkg.dev/<PROJECT>/<REPO>/{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/<hallmark>/vouch:<hallmark>`)
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if either vouch artifact is absent: emit clear message directing operator to run summon first; no network calls attempted

//axhos_step
. *Clean Previous Instance*:
.. {rbbc_call}
`docker compose ... down --remove-orphans` to remove any existing containers and networks for this nameplate's compose project
.. Tolerates missing project (first start)

//axhos_step
. *Detect Nameplate Collisions*:
.. Enumerate Docker networks bearing the `com.docker.compose.project` label; for each, read its `com.docker.compose.network` and `com.docker.compose.project` labels
.. Match: `com.docker.compose.network` is `enclave` or `transit` AND `com.docker.compose.project` matches `^(.*-)?{rbrn_moniker}$` (covers bare moniker from pre-prefix-era residue and any `{prefix}{rbrn_moniker}` form, since `{rbrr_runtime_prefix}` is constrained to end with `-`)
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if any foreign network matches: refusal lists each offending network name with the exact `docker network rm` command(s)
.. Independently, enumerate all Docker networks and inspect each for subnet match against `{rbrn_enclave_base_ip}/{rbrn_enclave_netmask}`; skip this nameplate's own compose network (already removed by prior step)
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if any foreign network occupies this subnet (catches non-compose networks not covered by the label-based scan)

//axhos_step
. *Start via Compose*:
.. {rbbc_call}
`docker compose --profile sessile up -d` with base compose file, optional nameplate fragment, and env-files for both repo regime and nameplate regime
.. Compose creates networks, starts sentry, waits for health, starts pentacle, waits for health, starts bottle
.. The `sessile` profile includes the bottle container; omitting it starts only sentry and pentacle (infrastructure mode for agile dispatch)

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution establishes a new
{at_sessile_service}
instance with the health check chain guaranteeing that security enforcement is active before the bottle starts.

//axhob_operation
{mkr_bottle_launch}

NOTE: Bottle container creation is managed by Docker Compose.
The bottle service definition specifies the bottle image, `network_mode: "service:pentacle"` (shares pentacle's network namespace), and a `sessile` profile gate.
Volume mounts are declared in the per-nameplate compose fragment (`«moniker».compose.yml`), not in nameplate env variables.

//axhos_step
. *Compose starts bottle after pentacle health check*:
.. The bottle's `depends_on` with `condition: service_healthy` ensures the pentacle has completed routing setup before the bottle starts
.. The bottle inherits the pentacle's network namespace — it sees the enclave interface with routing through the sentry already configured
.. No network configuration occurs inside the bottle container

//axhoc_completion
The bottle starts with a pre-configured network path through the sentry.
Security enforcement is active from the first packet.

//axhob_operation
{mkr_bottle_create}

NOTE: This sequence within
{rbsc_enjoin}
describes what Docker Compose does when creating a transient
{at_bottle_container}
via `docker compose run`.
Compose inherits the full bottle service definition — image, network mode, volumes, and dependencies — from the base compose file and optional nameplate fragment.

//axhos_step
. *Compose resolves container configuration*:
.. Image: `{rbrn_bottle_vessel}:{rbrn_bottle_hallmark}` from compose service definition
.. Network: inherits `network_mode: "service:pentacle"` (shares pentacle's network namespace, which routes through sentry)
.. Volumes: declared in per-nameplate compose fragment (`«moniker».compose.yml`), not in nameplate env variables
.. Environment: forwarded from compose env-files and service `environment:` section

//axhos_step
. *Compose creates transient container*:
.. Container created from resolved service definition with `--rm` (automatic removal on exit)
.. Compose assigns container name (not user-specified for transient runs)
.. {rbbc_require}
container created successfully

//axhoc_completion
Successful creation yields a transient container with the same security posture as a sessile bottle — same network namespace, same volume mounts, same sentry enforcement.

Variables in this group apply only when
{rbrn_entry_mode}
is
{rbrn_entry_mode_enabled}.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrn_entry_port_workstation}

External port exposed on the transit network for user entry.
Must be less than
{rbrn_uplink_port_min}.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrn_entry_port_enclave}

Port used between sentry and bottle containers for entry traffic.
Must be less than
{rbrn_uplink_port_min}.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrn_enclave_base_ip}

Base IPv4 address that defines the enclave network range.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrn_enclave_netmask}

Network mask width for the enclave network addressing.
Valid range: 8-30.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrn_enclave_sentry_ip}

IP address assigned to the sentry container for traffic mediation within the enclave.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrn_enclave_bottle_ip}

IP address assigned to the bottle container within the enclave.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrn_uplink_port_min}

Minimum port number for bottle-initiated outbound connections.
Must be greater than any entry port.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrn_uplink_dns_mode}

Selects DNS resolution behavior for bottle-initiated requests.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrn_uplink_access_mode}

Selects IP access behavior for bottle-initiated connections.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrn_group_access_allowlist}

